when the cat's watching me.

243
00:14:41,213 --> 00:14:43,249
Nobody answer the phone!

244
00:14:43,513 --> 00:14:46,152
Please, let it be her.
Please, please, please.

245
00:14:49,117 --> 00:14:51,187
No, wait.
Berta, you answer it.

246
00:14:51,710 --> 00:14:53,860
No, no, no! Let it ring.

247
00:14:54,345 --> 00:14:56,654
No, answer it.

248
00:14:56,938 --> 00:14:58,815
- Harper residence.
- I'm not here.

249
00:14:59,071 --> 00:15:01,426
- Yeah, he's here.
- Okay, I'm here.

250
00:15:01,998 --> 00:15:03,829
Jake, it's your mother!

251
00:15:05,511 --> 00:15:09,743
So how's it going down there?
You struck oil yet?

252
00:15:12,453 --> 00:15:14,728
Charlie, what is going on with you?

253
00:15:15,339 --> 00:15:18,012
- What?
- What do you mean, "what"?

254
00:15:18,308 --> 00:15:20,663
You're spending half your time
drinking and moping.

255
00:15:20,943 --> 00:15:22,774
The other half sleeping
and throwing up.

256
00:15:23,034 --> 00:15:25,184
You haven't been
out of the house all week.

257
00:15:25,460 --> 00:15:28,577
You want me
to go out like this in public?

258
00:15:29,433 --> 00:15:32,709
If you feel so strongly about this girl,
why don't you just call her?

259
00:15:33,029 --> 00:15:35,020
Yeah, sure, I could call her.

260
00:15:35,288 --> 00:15:38,519
I could also FedEx her my testicles
in a little silk bag.

261
00:15:40,432 --> 00:15:43,822
All the more reason to call first
and give her a heads-up.

262
00:15:44,154 --> 00:15:47,112
Alan, don't you understand?
This isn't about dating anymore.

263
00:15:47,416 --> 00:15:50,965
It's not even about sex.
It's about self-respect and pride.

264
00:15:51,556 --> 00:15:55,026
Yeah, well, I think
that ship has sailed, Charlie.

265
00:15:55,613 --> 00:15:59,367
See, the problem is
she doesn't need me.

266
00:16:00,046 --> 00:16:02,514
So I need to figure out
a way to show her...

267
00:16:02,806 --> 00:16:05,604
that I don't need her just as much
as she doesn't need me.

268
00:16:05,901 --> 00:16:08,017
But without seeming needy.

269
00:16:10,334 --> 00:16:12,450
You see my dilemma?

270
00:16:13,262 --> 00:16:15,617
Actually, I think I do.

271
00:16:15,896 --> 00:16:19,172
You feel like I felt
when Judith kicked me out.

272
00:16:20,371 --> 00:16:23,249
All right, if you're gonna mock me,
this conversation's over.

273
00:16:27,564 --> 00:16:31,193
- Who took my sandwich?
- Go do your homework.

274
00:16:32,374 --> 00:16:34,683
Unbelievable.

275
00:16:38,229 --> 00:16:41,426
- I'm glad you were free tonight.
- I'm glad I was home when you called.

276
00:16:41,742 --> 00:16:44,131
I would've called sooner,
but it's been a crazy week.

277
00:16:44,418 --> 00:16:46,170
It's okay. I understand.

278
00:16:46,426 --> 00:16:48,656
- Oh, Charlie, I want you.
- Are you sure?

279
00:16:48,935 --> 00:16:50,971
- Oh, yeah.
- How much?

280
00:16:51,235 --> 00:16:53,590
- Can't you tell?
- I wanna hear it.

281
00:16:53,870 --> 00:16:55,986
I need you. I ache for you.

282
00:16:56,714 --> 00:16:58,750
Okay, then.

283
00:17:01,607 --> 00:17:03,723
- What are you doing?
- I've gotta get home.

284
00:17:03,991 --> 00:17:05,663
I got an early meeting.

285
00:17:07,588 --> 00:17:10,056
- What?
- Beat you to it this time, didn't I?

286
00:17:11,435 --> 00:17:14,586
What are you talk...? What kind
of game are you playing here?

287
00:17:14,906 --> 00:17:18,615
The same game you're playing,
only tonight, I win.

288
00:17:19,548 --> 00:17:21,345
Really? What is it that you're winning?

289
00:17:21,598 --> 00:17:25,068
Charlie, I'm lying here hungry for
your body and you're walking away.

290
00:17:25,403 --> 00:17:28,156
So, what exactly is it
that you're winning?

291
00:17:33,559 --> 00:17:35,311
You know.

292
00:17:37,448 --> 00:17:39,279
- Get out.
- It's too late.

293
00:17:39,539 --> 00:17:42,099
You can't kick me out.
I already said I'm leaving.

294
00:17:57,564 --> 00:17:59,441
Hey.

295
00:17:59,697 --> 00:18:02,689
- So how'd it go?
- Great.

296
00:18:03,001 --> 00:18:05,674
I took control.
I regained my self-respect.

297
00:18:05,970 --> 00:18:08,086
I walked out of there
with my head held high.

298
00:18:08,354 --> 00:18:12,108
Good for you. Good for you.
So you're done beating yourself up?

299
00:18:13,247 --> 00:18:14,919
Not quite.

300
00:18:24,246 --> 00:18:26,043
Jake, wait till we get inside.

301
00:18:27,383 --> 00:18:30,341
I'm hungry.
Uncle Charlie's in there.

302
00:18:31,607 --> 00:18:33,040
I see your point.

303
00:18:33,279 --> 00:18:35,588
At the risk of asking
a foolish question...

304
00:18:35,872 --> 00:18:37,510
you got any homework
this weekend?

305
00:18:37,754 --> 00:18:40,826
- Nope. Did it at school.
- Really?

306
00:18:41,142 --> 00:18:46,455
- Yup. Did it during detention.
- Jake, why did you have detention?

307
00:18:46,871 --> 00:18:49,066
Because I didn't
do my homework yesterday.

308
00:18:49,883 --> 00:18:52,602
So you did yesterday's homework
and today's homework?

309
00:18:52,894 --> 00:18:55,169
Yup. The extra-credit section
and everything.

310
00:18:55,445 --> 00:18:59,882
- Oh, great. I'll look it over.
- Okay, I didn't do it.

311
00:19:01,174 --> 00:19:04,564
- Jake, why do you keep lying?
- Because I thought you trusted me.

312
00:19:07,113 --> 00:19:09,946
The detention part was true.

313
00:19:13,219 --> 00:19:15,096
Hi, Charlie.

314
00:19:15,352 --> 00:19:17,912
Hey, Rose. What's going on?

315
00:19:18,196 --> 00:19:21,074
I just stopped by to say I'm sorry
things didn't work out...

316
00:19:21,374 --> 00:19:24,207
with you and Sherri.
- Yeah. Thanks.

317
00:19:24,511 --> 00:19:27,309
And I'm sorry for my
schadenfreude the other day.

318
00:19:27,605 --> 00:19:30,881
I've been riddled with
"glaukenschtuken" ever since.

319
00:19:31,202 --> 00:19:33,841
- Glauken...?
- Schtuken.

320
00:19:34,129 --> 00:19:37,724
It means: " Feeling guilty
for having felt schadenfreude."

321
00:19:38,479 --> 00:19:40,435
- They've got a word for that?
- Not yet.

322
00:19:40,695 --> 00:19:43,528
But I'm hoping
"glaukenschtuken" catches on.

323
00:19:44,878 --> 00:19:47,153
I'll do my part.

324
00:19:48,181 --> 00:19:51,457
You know, something good
did come out of all this:

325
00:19:52,238 --> 00:19:54,149
Watching you obsess over Sherri...

326
00:19:54,413 --> 00:19:57,246
really helped me understand
my obsession for you.

327
00:19:57,549 --> 00:20:01,337
I mean, you never return my calls.
You always see other women.

328
00:20:01,690 --> 00:20:03,760
You never knowingly
let me sleep over.

329
00:20:05,872 --> 00:20:09,387
And yet, I've never been able
to get you out of my head.

330
00:20:10,681 --> 00:20:12,558
- Interesting.
- Isn't it?

331
00:20:12,814 --> 00:20:17,444
But now that I understand it,
I feel somehow free of it.

332
00:20:18,084 --> 00:20:21,394
Well, that's great, Rose. It sounds
like a real healthy breakthrough.

333
00:20:21,722 --> 00:20:26,318
Yeah. And the best part is now
that the fog of obsession has lifted...

334
00:20:26,699 --> 00:20:31,136
I can stop idealizing you,
and see you for who you really are.

335
00:20:32,512 --> 00:20:34,662
And who would that be?

336
00:20:34,938 --> 00:20:38,977
An emotionally scarred
and deeply flawed human being.

337
00:20:39,914 --> 00:20:42,712
Who will one day bless me...

338
00:20:43,009 --> 00:20:47,048
with emotionally scarred
and deeply flawed children.

339
00:20:49,282 --> 00:20:50,601
Rose.

340
00:20:51,917 --> 00:20:54,147
Just hold me.

341
00:20:56,643 --> 00:20:59,999
I like the names Mike and Trudy.

